surf_report.summary: 13th beach has a light offshore and a very small swell at 1ft that is struggling to break and really just lapping on the shore.Best options will be the beachies but take something around 15 ft with a motor. Down south would have waves but that's a serious road trip and a commitment of a full day.The low tide is 9.10 am with a 0.55 metres and the high tide is 4.05 pm with a 1.62 metres. Looks like the swell will build a little by Wednesday though winds will likely be variable...

image.text: A slow moving trough is triggering isolated storms from the NSW coast to western QLD. A low in the southeast is weakening, causing showers in TAS to ease. Dry southeasterlies in VIC and SA. A deep trough in WA brings storms while a front pushes blustery showers over the southwestThe northern jet is helping showers and storms develop near the surface trough in NSW and western QLD. The polar jet is taking a low across the Tasman Sea and is also directing another low and front towards southwest WA.
